cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with a network of Mobile Aerial Agents (MAAs) and proposes a distributed control law to adjust their spatial coordinates. This falls under the domain of robotics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper discusses the problem of visual area coverage by a network of MAAs equipped with cameras. This involves computer vision techniques for image processing and analysis. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed control law aims to maximize a joint coverage-quality criterion, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper deals with a network of MAAs that collaborate to achieve a common objective. This falls under the domain of multi-agent systems. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper involves visualization of the covered area by the MAAs, which may involve graphics techniques for displaying the results.
